div.p:
“How very handsome he is,” she said to herself, as she ran up the house‐steps;
                    “how agreeable—and I don’t feel sure he will make himself agreeable next
                    time—that makes one curious to be with him again.”

“No one is listening to us,” said Leslie, “no one can tell what we are saying;
                    the insufferable drumming of the piano‐forte prevents the human voice from being
                    heard.”

“Oh! never think that again—be my wife, and such thoughts could never come—there
                    would be but one thought between us, neither you could doubt me, nor I you;
                    would not there be a pleasure in that?”
